        "rules": "The person who played this card leads the running count in Ojibwe. Each player takes a turn saying a number until they reach 9 as a group. The first person to say a number wrong, draws a card and the count ends. If the count is successful, the leader picks a player to pick up 2 cards. The game continues as normal. Example: Person 1 “Bezhig”, Person 2 “Niizh”, Person 3 “Niswi”, Person 4 “Niiwin”, Person 1 “Naanan” and so forth.",
